        1. Use web_search to find relevant, up-to-date information (run several
           searches with varied queries to get broad coverage).
        2. Use fetch_page to read the most promising URLs returned by search.
        3. Use add_note to record every key finding (cite the source URL).
        4. After you have gathered enough material (at least 3-5 good sources),
           use read_notes to review everything you collected.
        5. Produce a well-structured summary with sections, bullet points, and
           source citations.
